      <h2 id="ios-dev">iOS Developer</h2>

      <h3>About the role</h3>
      <p>You will be solely responsible for the development of our green-field iOS app.</p>
      <p>You will therefore be involved in everything; developing the intial app from the ground up; integrating and maintaining various APIs; co-designing the UI to optimise performance and delight users; safeguarding the availability of our service.</p>
      <p>You will also own the mobile application development and deployment cycles - including our beta testing programme and app store submissions.</p>
      <h3>You must have</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Track record of building rich, engaging iOS apps that delight users, including at least one app built in Swift</li>
        <li>You will be comfortable managing an effective development and deployment process and understand the value of testing.</li>
        <li>A passion for UI &amp; UX (creating UI components, animations and transitions is essential, as is being comfortable with autolayout) – after all it’s not just how it’s built, but how people use it.</li>
        <li>A strong sense of ownership, urgency, and drive – you shouldn’t be afraid to wear many hats and get your hands dirty.</li>
        <li>You must have strong analytical and troubleshooting skills as well as fluent written and verbal communication.</li>
        <li>Experience with game design is a definite plus.</li>
      </ul>
      <h3>Benefits</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Competitive salary with equity options</li>
        <li>Get in on the ground floor of an exciting new start-up, with a truly disruptive proposition</li>
        <li>It’s a completely green-field project, so the architecture and design is entirely up to you (although the user should alway be front of mind)!</li>
        <li>Work at Runway East - home to some of the UK’s hottest start-ups</li>
      </ul>
      <h3>Your application should include</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Your CV, along with your GitHub URL</li>
        <li>Links to apps you have created worked on</li>
      </ul>
